timeline.bodyText:
A testing technique - a problem with assertTrue/assertFalse is that if it fails, it's not known why. We really want to see the value of indexConfig to find out what's going on.
To improve on that, I'd do this:
["someProperty", "someOtherProperty", etc].forEach(prop -> {
    assertTrue(indexConfig.contains(property), "Expected " + property + " to be in indexConfig: " + indexConfig);
});

That makes debugging a test failure much easier.

