timeline.bodyText:
There's no need to define these ahead of time. Just assign properties directly to "result", makes for less code - i.e. declare "result" as:
result = {
  protectedPaths: [],
  queryRolesets: [],
  index-config: {},
  options: {}
};

That also has a nice benefit of immediately telling the reader what the response object looks like.

